    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And their words pleased Hamor, and Shechem Hamor\u2019s son.] The condition proposed was acceptable to them both, and they agreed to comply with it; Hamor, because of the great love he had for his son; Shechem, because of the great love he had for Dinah.\nVer.\n18. Give Bible proof that troglodytes (cave dwellers) were not separated in incalculable periods of time from. highly developed and civilized types, but were contemporaries.",
