    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Hamor communed with them, etc.] With Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` and his sons, who came in just at that time: saying, the soul of my son Shechem longeth for your daughter: the daughter of the family, and the only daughter in it; for her Shechem had a vehement affection, a strong desire to marry her, and could not be satisfied without her: I pray you, give her him to wife; he not only requests the consent of the parents of the damsel, but of her brothers also, which in those times and 598 countries seems to have been usual to ask and have, (see <012450>Genesis 24:50,51,55,59).\nVer.\n8. Is the second chapter an independent and conflicting account of creation?",
