    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "King Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` took a few minutes to digest the truth he had just recorded (vs. 11), and, then, as a postscript, he decides that even if \u201csentence\u201d is not executed speedily on the wicked, sooner or later he will \u201cget what\u2019s coming to him.\u201d Notice the division of thought at this point: 1. \u201cThough a sinner...his days be prolonged.\u201d 2. \u201cNeither shall he prolong his days\u201d (vs. 13). Can you guess what will happen to the faculty members of Princeton, Grace Theological Seminary, Liberty University, Bob Jones University, Wheaton, Fuller, Moody, and Baptist Bible College, when they \u201cface off\u2019 with these two conflicting statements? By now, you shouldn\u2019t have to guess. The name of the game is \u201cReduce the serious student of Scripture to the level of stupidity attained by the Hebrew and Greek scholars on the faculty.\u201d The Girl Scouts (see Problem Texts,\n11. King Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]` took a few minutes to digest the truth he had just recorded (vs. 11), and, then, as a postscript, he decides that even if \u201csentence\u201d is not executed speedily on the wicked, sooner or later he will \u201cget what\u2019s coming to him.\u201d Notice the division of thought at this point: 1. \u201cThough a sinner...his days be prolonged.\u201d 2. \u201cNeither shall he prolong his days\u201d (vs. 13). Can you guess what will happen to the faculty members of Princeton, Grace Theological Seminary, Liberty University, Bob Jones University, Wheaton, Fuller, Moody, and Baptist Bible College, when they \u201cface off\u2019 with these two conflicting statements? By now, you shouldn\u2019t have to guess. The name of the game is \u201cReduce the serious student of Scripture to the level of stupidity attained by the Hebrew and Greek scholars on the faculty.\u201d The Girl Scouts (see Problem Texts,",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Shechem said unto her father and unto her brethren, etc.] To the father and brethren of Dinah; he addressed them after his father Hamor had done speaking: let me find grace in your eyes; forgive the offence committed, the injury done to Dinah, and grant the request of her marriage, and it will be considered as a great favour: and what ye shall say unto me, I will give; to her, to her parents, to her brethren and relations; let what will be fixed, shall be given; which showed great affection for her, and that he was willing to do any thing to make 599 amends for the injury done; he cared not what it was that might be demanded of him, so be it that she became his wife.\nVer.\n11. What details are supplied in the second chapter not found in the first chapter?",
    "Commentary Vol. 84": "Who wrestled with Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` and what is the key to Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]`'s power?"
