    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Head of a Gadite family. 1 Chr. 5: 13.\n3. He is called MATHUSALA in Luke 3:\n3. Persian king who &quot;reigned from India even unto Ethiopia,&quot; and took the Jewish maiden Esther `[char_Esther_Ref]` to be his queen. He is held to have been Xerxes, son of Darius Hystaspis. This was in the seventh year of his reign, the year when he returned from his unsuccessful expedition against Greece. His rash conduct in repudiating his queen because she would not violate the decorum of her sex, and his giving up the whole of the Jewish people to the pride of Haman, agrees with his folly in scourging the sea and putting the engineers to death because a storm injured the bridge they had made. See ESTHER. For the succession of the Persian kings see PERSIA. Ahava. [A'hava] Place or river near which Ezra rested 3 days prior to his journey from Babylon to Jerusalem. Ezra 8: 15, 21,\n3. Descendant of Benjamin. 1 Chr. 8:\n3. City whose king was killed under Joshua, but whether the same as either of the above is unknown. Joshua 12: 17.",
